		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Camping T-Staff<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jul 23rd 4:59 AM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=10589501345603&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=10589501345603&num=0&post=1&replyto=10589501345603"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10589501345603></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=36958"><span id=Scholar>Beemo</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>176 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Beemo&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I posted this on monkly-business also...<br><br>I recommend any level 57 (well equiped) and up who either wants a T-Staff or just wants to sell them to give this a shot. Also recommend having regen (item, AAs etc..) and many bandages.<br><br>T-Staff is a very rare drop off Skeletal Warlords (SW) in Karanors Castle. The SW themselves are pretty rare to boot but have numerous spawn points. They can spawn on the bridge outside of LCY and RCY, Well room and the Jail area. I recommend camping the Jail area because it has 5 possible spawn spots in a confined area. This spot is usually open for the most part unless there is a group in Drolvarg Warlord room claiming dibbs.<br><br>Getting to the jail can be a pain. The most common path to take is across bridges, through LCY, upstairs to Skel Tower, past hands and to Jail. KC is such a train feast that most of the time you can wait for someone to train the mobs you need to avoid to zone and hightail it to the jail before the mobs head back. If not, take it slow. Let each area you are passing know that you are coming through. DON'T TRAIN! Its not necessary, /q if you have to. Once you pass Skel Tower, make sure you stay on the right wall passing the door to hands. Hands will aggro if you get close to the door. After you pass the door to hands, hug the left wall to the jail and keep an eye out for roamers. There are 2 roamers in this area and they can be any mob in the zone except basement mobs. If any of the roaming mobs are casters, KILL them. The Curates will CH the jail mobs and the Callers will Haste and Heal the Jail mobs. <br><br>SIDE NOTE: Callers have pets with them. If you kill the Caller, and FD, the pet will stay in one spot and is KOS to all mobs in the zone but not to you! That means you can punch the dog, have it chase you to the jail and FD. The dog will attack any mob you bring it to. Get up, take aggro from the dog and you are now a monk with a pet! It helps.<br><br>When you get to the jail, there are 5 cells. All have mobs in them. I find it easier to run all the way to the end and FD. Wait for them to return to spawn points, get up and start the first cell. The only mobs that can spawn in the Jail are Drolvarg Guardians, Skeletal Guardians or SW. In the middle cell there is a quest NPC that spawns, A Human Skeleton, but he drops crap and just takes up a possible spawn for the SW...so killem. Time your kills. Spend some time Bandaging working on other skills. Each cell is a 26 min respawn. You can reasonably knock out all cells in 10 min but who wants to sit around for 16 min. Once you have the cells split, double check that your roamers are non-caster types, if they are, leave them alone.<br><br>The SW can drop Deepwater Boots, Dwarven Sapp, Jarsath Wrists, T-Staff and No-drop Bone Chips. Other possible loot is Elder Spiritualist Gauntlets, Flayed Skin Stuff...some plat, FS Weapons. Its not all that crappy for PP, and exp (up to level 60). This could take days but the possible pay off is an easy to obtain 25K item. I have gotten 2 in one week.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Quanko Crakkers<br>65 Grandmaster<br>(<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87045" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87045</a><br>Xegony</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a clas